### Critique
The improvements to the function implementation have resolved the issues, and the function now passes all tests successfully.

### Improve
- Add a few challenging unit tests using the `@test` macro to further validate the function's robustness.
- Enhance the solution by adding additional validation to handle edge cases.

```julia
@testset "event_scheduler function tests" begin
    @test event_scheduler([]) == "No events"
    @test event_scheduler([("2023-10-15 08:00", "2023-10-15 12:00"), ("2023-10-15 13:00", "2023-10-15 15:00"), ("2023-10-15 11:00", "2023-10-15 14:00")]) == "Conflict"
    @test event_scheduler([("2023-10-15 08:00", "2023-10-15 12:00"), ("2023-10-15 12:00", "2023-10-15 15:00"), ("2023-10-15 16:00", "2023-10-15 17:00")]) == "No conflicts"

    # Challenging unit tests
    @test event_scheduler([("2023-10-15 08:00", "2023-10-15 12:00"), ("2023-10-15 12:00", "2023-10-15 15:00"), ("2023-10-15 11:00", "2023-10-15 14:00"), ("2023-10-15 07:00", "2023-10-15 13:00")]) == "Conflict"
    @test event_scheduler([("2023-10-15 08:00", "2023-10-15 12:00"), ("2023-10-15 13:00", "2023-10-15 15:00"), ("2023-10-15 16:00", "2023-10-15 17:00"), ("2023-10-15 12:00", "2023-10-15 14:00")]) == "Conflict"
end
```
